<taxonomicName authority="(Pfeffer, 1887)" authorityName="Pfeffer" authorityYear="1887" baseAuthorityName="Pfeffer" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[151,598,542,567]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Chorismus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antarcticus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,598,542,567]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,419,542,567]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Chorismus antarcticus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[433,590,542,567]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" refId="ref25783" refString="Pfeffer, G. (1887) Die Krebse von Sud-Georgien nach der Ausbeute der Deutschen Station 1882 - 83. Jahrbuch der wissenschaftlichen Anstalten zu Hamburg, 4, 1 - 110, pls. 1 - 7. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 10084" type="journal article">Pfeffer, 1887</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,542,783]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">
A circum-Antarctic benthic shelf species (
<quantity box="[634,740,578,603]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.575" metricValueMax="9.15" metricValueMin="0.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" unit="m" value="457.5" valueMax="915.0" valueMin="0.0">0–915 m</quantity>
), reaching South Georgia, the Falkland Islands and Southern Patagonia (
<bibRefCitation box="[278,445,614,639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" refId="ref23038" refString="Holthuis, L. B. (1952) Reports of the Lund University Chile Expedition 1948 - 1949. 5. The Crustacea Decapoda Macrura of Chile. Lunds Universitets Arsskrift, N. F., Avd. 2, 47 (10), 1 - 110." type="journal article">Holthuis 1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[457,653,614,639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" refId="ref21533" refString="Garth, J. S., Haig, J. &amp; Yaldwyn, J. C. (1967) The Decapod Crustacea of the Royal Society Expedition to Southern Chile, 1958 - 59. Transactions of the Royal Society of New Zealand, Zoology, 8 (16), 169 - 186." type="journal article">
Garth 
<emphasis box="[529,586,614,639]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[664,826,614,639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" refId="ref24432" refString="Ledoyer, M. (1989) Mysidacea et Caridea (Crustacea) de la campagne MD 42 / Sibex du &quot; Marion-Dufresne &quot; entre les Iles Kerguelen et la baie Prydz (Antarctique). Mesogee, 49, 67 - 70." type="journal article">Ledoyer 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[838,1047,614,639]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" refId="ref23876" refString="Komai, T., Takeuchi, I. &amp; Takeda, M. (1996) Deep-sea shrimp (Crustacea: Decapoda: Caridea) from the Antarctic Sea collected during the JARE- 35 cruise. Proceedings of the NIPR Symposium on Polar Biology, Tokyo, 9, 179 - 206." type="journal article">
Komai 
<emphasis box="[922,979,614,639]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
1996
</bibRefCitation>
), although possibly confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[151,329,650,675]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Chorismus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuberculatus">
<emphasis box="[151,329,650,675]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">C. tuberculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sub-Antarctic areas. Biological differences were observed between populations from South Georgia and the Weddell Sea (
<bibRefCitation box="[498,706,686,711]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" refId="ref21636" refString="Gorny, M., Arntz, W. E., Clarke, A. &amp; Gore, D. J. (1992) Reproductive biology of caridean decapods from the Weddell Sea. Polar Biology, 12 (1), 111 - 120. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / 0022 - 0981 (93) 90021 - F" type="journal article">
Gorny 
<emphasis box="[580,638,686,711]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">et al.</emphasis>
1992
</bibRefCitation>
). A very common species, with a preference for bottoms rich in epifauna (personal observations of the first author). Synonym: 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Milne-Edwards, 1891" authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1891" box="[892,1436,722,747]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hippolytidae" genus="Hippolyte" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="romanchei">
<emphasis box="[892,1136,722,747]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="223">Hippolyte romanchei</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1146,1436,722,747]" pageId="22" pageNumber="223" refId="ref25217" refString="Milne-Edwards, A. (1891) Crustaces. Mission scientifique du Cap-Horn 1882 - 1883. Tome VI. Zoologie. Ministere de la Marine et de l'Instruction Publique, Paris, 76 pp., 84 pls." type="book chapter">A. Milne-Edwards, 1891</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(type locality: Tierra del Fuego).
</paragraph>
